    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>The most populated city in the state of Idaho, Boise is home to over 610,500 people, making
it the third most populated metropolitan area in the United States Pacific Northwest region.
A mostly mild climate, the summers are dry and hot, the winters cold and wet. A cultural
hub, there is public art all downtown, adding an artistic touch to the natural beauty of the
area. There are many parks with facilities that cater to any outdoor activity one could
imagine; golf, pools, soccer, softball, fishing, tennis, basketball, baseball, bird watching,
archery and much more! Downtown Boise is home to many different local restaurants,
bars, boutiques and shops. There is also the Egyptian Theatre, which opened in 1927, and
the Boise Art Museum, showing interesting breathtaking exhibits year round. With a local
art center and community center, there is a sense of unity and pride throughout the city that
is contagious to those who visit. Come see what's happening in Boise!</p>
