    <h3>District Information</h3>
    <p>One of the oldest and largest school districts in Idaho, the Independent School District
serves 25,000 students. With a commitment to providing the finest education available
and possible for each student, the teachers and staff are dedicated to educating today for
a better tomorrow. Teaching students about the districts core values is a top priority, as
they become traits that are the basis for a successful future. Encouraging respect, dignity,
honesty, and responsibility and emphasizing the importance of teamwork, that is the
mission of this district. Fostering personal, emotional and intellectual growth is seen as
another pivotal step in the route to a bright tomorrow. Preparing students for life in the
21st century, a variety of specialized art classes are offered, as well as student run clubs and
organizations. There are seasonal sports played as well, with athletes pushing themselves
in regional and national competitions every year. With clear goals and the right tools, the
Independent School District delivers excellence to its students.</p>
